cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CVPR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with object detection from a single image using depth information. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper discusses the application of the proposed method in autonomous driving. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper proposes a new local convolutional network that can automatically learn filters from depth maps. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with improving the accuracy of 3D object detection using a novel approach. 
5. cs.CVPR (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a possible category as the paper presents experimental results on the KITTI dataset, which is commonly used in CVPR research.
